solutions.content:
For any String you can move any char to anywhere if you can swap adjacent characters

For any String `abc[XY]def` you can always do following to swap `XY` if k > 1

1. `abc[XY]def` original string
2. `[XY]defabc` move `a` to the end, `b` to the end, `c` to the end, etc.
3. `defabc[YX]` move `Y` to the end, we can do it because k > 1, then move `X` to the end.
4. `abc[YX]def` move `d` to the end, `e` to the end, `f` to the end, etc.

```
    public String orderlyQueue(String s, int k) {
        if (k > 1) {
            char[] arr = s.toCharArray();
            Arrays.sort(arr);
            return String.valueOf(arr);
        } else {
            String min = s;
            for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
                s = s.substring(1) + s.charAt(0);
                min = min.compareTo(s) < 0 ? min : s;
            }
            return min;
        }
    }
```

