solutions.content:
1. Basic idea is bubble sort
 **CASE 1: if K>=2**
2. if we can swap any two consecutive character i.e we can do a sort then.
  eg: aa**db**ac lets try to swap d and b  k=2
      step1 : adbaca
      step2:  dbacaa
     step 3: dacaab
     step 4: acaabd
     step5 : caabda
     step6 : aa**bd**ac  
   if K is greater than equal to 2 we can swap any 2 consecutive character. so we can use sorting then.

**CASE2: if K ==1**
  now we cannot swap any 2 consecutive characters so we have to check for all combinations and check which is lexographically smallest.


```
class Solution {
    public String orderlyQueue(String S, int K) {
        if(K>=2){
            char[] ch=S.toCharArray();
            Arrays.sort(ch);
            return new String(ch);
        }else{
            String s2=S + S;
            for(int i=0;i<S.length();i++){
                String temp=s2.substring(i,i+S.length());
                S=(S.compareTo(temp)>0)?temp:S;
            }
        }
        return S;
    }
}
```

**TIME COMPLEXITY : 
if K>=2 O(NLogN)**
**if K==1 O(N^2) (bcz compareTO O(N))   for every possible combination we are doing  a O(N) operation so time complexity is O(N^2)**

SPACE COMPLEXITY : O(1)

