solutions.content:
**Idea:**
If `k==1`, then we can only choose the first letter and append it to the end. This is basically rotating the string. So we can just try rotating and see the smallest result.
If `k>1`, then we can do some amount of moves to always get the string sorted.
We can keep 1 or more numbers in the beginning of the string and take care only of the rest.
```
class Solution {
public:
    string orderlyQueue(string s, int k) {
        if (k > 1) {
            sort(s.begin(), s.end());
            return s;
        }

        string res = s;
        for (int i = 0; i < s.size(); i++)
            res = min(res, s.substr(i)+s.substr(0, i));
        return res;
    }
};
```
