# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
There is one catch in this problem.
If k>1 then the answer always sorted order, So
just sort the string and return that string
If K==1 then you have to traverse string and find lexicographically smallest string, it's not defficult.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
 if K==0 then simply return that string.
 if K>1 sort the string and return that string.
 if K==1 finds all such combinations and return lexicographically the smallest string.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
Time complexity O(n^2) if k==1
and O(nlogn) if k>1

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
Space complexity O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    string orderlyQueue(string s, int k) 
    {
        if(k==0)
        {
            return s;
        }
        if(k>1)
        {
            sort(s.begin(),s.end());
            return s;
        }
        if(k==1)
        {
            string st=s;
            for (int i=0;i<s.length()-1;i++)
            {
                string p=s.substr(i+1,s.length())+s.substr(0,i+1);
                if(st>p){
                    st=p;
                }
            }
            return st;
        }
        return s;

    }
};
```

