**Intuition**
when ```k >= 2```, when can swap any two adjancent letters. For example, we want to swap ```C``` and ```D```in string ```ABCDEDF```. then we can do:  ```ABCDEDF``` => ```CDEDFAB``` =>  ```CEDFABD``` => =>  ```EDFABDC``` => ```ABDCEDF```

when ```k = 1```, when can only append the first letter to the end every time.
**Implementation**
```
public class Solution {
    public string OrderlyQueue(string s, int k) {

        if(k >= 2)
        {
            char[] arr = s.ToCharArray();
            Array.Sort(arr);
            return new string(arr);
        }
        else
        {
            string min = s;
            for(int i = 0; i < s.Length; i++)
            {
                s = s.Substring(1, s.Length - 1) + s[0];
                if(s.CompareTo(min) < 0)
                    min = s;
            }
            return min;
        }
    }
}
```

