/*

Before Jump to the problem let's discuss some cases which may tell us how to proceed to this problem.

EXAMPLE->1: s="bcabc"  k=1
-----------
 now pick index 0 character 'b' and append at the end of the string. s="cabcb"

 again pick index 0 character 'c' and append it then s="abcbc".

 This modified string is the lexicographically smallest among all the permutations possible by k-moves any number of times.

 So,when k is given k=1  , Then we observe that 

 we are allowed to rotate the string any number of time by 1 character [Left Rotation]

 So just apply brute force method to check which rotated string gives us the desired output.


 EXAMPLE->2: s="bcaaaaa"  k=2
 ----------

 When we are given k==2 in other word it gives us the freedom to swap any two adjacent characters . And obvoiusly for our sake we sort two characters lexicographically at each move . As a result, second smallest character comes after smallest character and the third one comes after second smallest character. 

 So required transformation looks like---->

 "bcaaaaa" ---  "caaaaab"  ---  "aaaaabc".

 So as a whole Just we can sort the string and return it.

 In a same manner for k>2 alse we can do the above mentioned steps (because the steps we follow for k==2 , we can repeat the same for k>2 also).


*/



