In fact when `K>1`, we can totally sort the string.

By swapping two neighbors, we can sort a string -- this is the way how **bubble sorting** works.
And by choosing one of two neighbors and place it at the end, we can rearrange/swap these two elements -- therefore we can sort the string when `K>=2`.

So the only part we need to deal with is when `K===1`.
