# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
If the value of k>1, no matter what the string is, it is possible to sort the entire string and return it.
Let's say, for eg:
```
String: baaca k=2
```
We can make the following transitions:
```
bacaa
bcaaa
caaab
aaabc
```
Thus if k>1, just sort the string and return it.
Otherwise, if k=1, send each character one by one, at the end of the string and check if the resultant string formed is lexicographically smallest string or not.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(NlogN)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
