The main intuition of this problem is finding that we can achieve the sorted form of the string if value of k is greater than 2

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/64ab1e04-296a-4e65-8768-056f6e7cb451_1630834404.4791017.png)

Therefore, for every string s , if **k >= 2** . The final answer will be the sorted order of that string

For **k == 1**, we can consider every possible ways and find the solution 

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/107307f7-b999-4fd3-988f-1ea8fa617fee_1630834518.059623.png)

***Time complexity :*** O(n + n log n)
***Space complexity :*** O(1)

```
class Solution:
    def orderlyQueue(self, s: str, k: int) -> str:
        if k==1:
            best = s
            for i in range(len(s)):
                cur = s[i:]+s[:i] 
                if cur<best : best = cur
            return best

        return "".join(sorted(s))
```

