/**
We take reverse of given string and try to find longest-common subsequence (LCS).

For example:- 

String s < - >  reverse of s
leetcode < - > edocteel
leETcodE < - > EdocTEel

so LCS is "e t e" and if we remove it from the 2 words, we are left with

letcod  < - >   docel


If a string is palindrome then its reverse would also be palindrome, 
or in other words each character would be present in order in both of the Strings.

String left after removing th LCS chars is nothing but those characters which are not present in order in its reversed
String.
It means if we insert "letcod" into "edocteel" or "docel" into "leetcode" then we would have our palindrome strings.

Here we insert "docel" into "leetcode".
l e e D O C t c o d e E L   <-Palindrome



Conclusion:-  Find length of LCS,  subtract it from given string length and we have our answer. 

