# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
This question is a **variation of longest palindromic subsequence**(Q.no- 516).
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Find the length of LCS of given string and it's reverse. The **difference of the length of string and the LCS will give minimum no. of insertions and deletion** in the string to make it a palindrome
# Complexity
- Time complexity: **O(n*n)**
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
- Space complexity: **O(n*n)**
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int LCS(string a,string b)
    {
        int n=a.size(),m=b.size();
        int t[n+1][m+1];
        for(int i=0;i<n+1;i++)
            t[i][0]=0;
        for(int j=0;j<m+1;j++)
            t[0][j]=0;
        for(int i=1;i<n+1;i++)
            for(int j=1;j<m+1;j++)
            {
                if(a[i-1]==b[j-1])
                    t[i][j]=1+t[i-1][j-1];
                else
                    t[i][j]=max(t[i-1][j],t[i][j-1]);
            }
        return t[n][m];

    }
    int minInsertions(string s) {
        int l=s.size();
        if(l==1)
        return 0;
        string sr;
        sr.append(s);
        reverse(s.begin(),s.end());
        return l-LCS(s,sr);
    }
};
```

