# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
my idea was that when checking if the string is a palindrom, starting with two pointers at the end and start of the string, if the characters at the two pointers arent equal you are presented with two options.

1. insertion of the right pointer character behind left pointer
2. insertion of the left pointer character in front of right pointer

calculating these two sub problems and choosing the minimum of the two gives you the least number of insertions for the string at given left pointer and right pointer.
# Approach
actually inserting the character into the string is done logically, but in the code is not actually needed since we are never interacting with characters behind our left pointer or in front of our right pointer.

dynamic programming is used here to store the results from the sub-problem calculations mentioned in the intuituion, if we calculated the best number of insertions for a unique left and right pointer, we shouldn't need to calculate it again.

NOTE: my solution was TLE for a while and it made me very sad :((, stopped TLE when I passed the string by reference since we aren't modifiying it :))))!

