solutions.content:
If `encoded[i] = arr[i] XOR arr[i + 1]` then we need to use inverse XOR to get the answer `arr[i + 1]`.
Surprisingly the inverse operation of XOR is XOR.
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/8e350914-87cb-4fd2-b934-b1f7636b191a_1656669386.0482025.jpeg)

So to get `arr[i + 1]` we need to just change places of the variables: `arr[i + 1] =  arr[i] XOR encoded[i]`.
P.S. I chose `arr[i + 1]` and not `arr[i]` because we are decoding and the arr[0] is already know, so we start right from the `arr[1] = arr[0] XOR encoded[0]`.

```
const decode = (encoded, first) => {
    let arr = [first];
    for (let i = 0; i < encoded.length; i++) {
        arr[i + 1] = arr[i] ^ encoded[i];
    }
    return arr;
};
```

