<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
As already stated 
encoded[i] = arr[i] XOR arr[i + 1]. 
From this statement we can easily say : 
arr[i] = arr[i-1] XOR encoded[i-1]

# Intution:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
We are already provided with arr[0]. According to question to get encoded[i] we need to know arr[i] and arr[i-1]. 

Let's see how we get encoded[0] for encoded[1,2,3] with arr[1,0,2,1] :
``` 
1 ^ 0 = 1 // arr[i] = arr[i-1] XOR encoded[i-1]

We are already provided with first element of arr[0]. 
To find arr[1] we can do arr[0] XOR encoded[0].
```
